The wait for this place is honestly a little insane for a place like this in Brooklyn. On a Friday night it was about a 45 minute wait and super noisy. Compared to other Mexican places, I honestly have to say that this is one of the best.  I ordered the Classic Cali, Cabo, and Diablo Diego Shrimp which were all $4.50 for one piece, which is a bit pricey but worth it because they are not cheap with the ingredients! Plus they're really juicy and delicious.  Nachos ($8.95)- 5/5 These are the best nachos- it comes out hot and has guac, black beans, cheese,pico de gallo, pickled jalapeno and you can even add protein in it, if you'd like. They also give you sour cream and salsa on the side. The portion was perfect for two people to share.  The Bombora- 3.5/5 This is their Friday special. It's quite a big burger and the fish comes out super hot. Wasn't too crazy about this burger, but it wasn't bad either.  Mango Iced Tea ($3.50)- 3.5/5 I thought this would be a light mango flavor but it was quite pungent, and it was a bit too sweet for my liking. If you love mango, this would be a perfect drink. I had to dilute it a bit.

I almost forgot it was freezing cold weather in bay ridge Brooklyn. Once you walk in and sit down, the restaurant makes you feel like you are at a beach down in the tropics after a long day of surfing.  Now the food, I tried the locos frites (tostones topped with all the essentials), Long Beach all star, Cabo, and Cali tacos. The fried plantains were awesome, served perfectly with the toppings and a creamy avocado sauce. Out of the tacos, my favorite would be the cali fish and steak tacos. Actually all were pretty good! They don't skimp on the fillings either so it's a decent sized taco.  I would definitely recommend coming here at least once if you are in bay ridge! They even have a lunch special if you work in the area.
